recipes.name: Spaghetti Carbonara
instructions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add spaghetti and cook according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.
Crack eggs into a bowl, add grated Parmesan cheese and freshly ground black pepper. Whisk until well combined and smooth.
In a large skillet, cook diced pancetta over medium heat until it becomes crispy and golden brown. Remove from heat and set aside, leaving the rendered fat in the skillet.
Quickly add the hot spaghetti to the skillet with pancetta fat. Pour the egg mixture over the spaghetti and toss rapidly to coat the pasta without scrambling the eggs.
Continue tossing until the sauce thickens and becomes creamy. Serve immediately with extra Parmesan and black pepper if desired.

recipes.name: Chicken Tikka Masala
instructions: In a bowl, combine chicken pieces, yogurt, lemon juice, minced garlic, grated ginger, cumin, coriander, and turmeric. Mix well, cover, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Preheat the grill or oven. Cook the marinated chicken until fully cooked and slightly charred. Set aside.
In a large pan, sauté chopped onions until translucent. Add minced garlic, grated ginger, and spices like cumin, coriander, and turmeric. Cook until fragrant.
Add tomato puree to the pan and simmer until thickened. Stir in cooked chicken pieces and heavy cream. Simmer for a few more minutes until the flavors meld together. Serve with rice or naan.

recipes.name: Sushi Rolls
instructions: Rinse sushi rice under cold water until the water runs clear. Cook according to package instructions. While still warm, gently mix with sushi vinegar and let it cool to room temperature.
Place a sheet of nori seaweed on a bamboo sushi mat, shiny side down.
With wet hands, spread a thin, even layer of sushi rice over the nori, leaving a small border at the top.
Place thin slices of salmon, avocado, and cucumber in a line along the bottom edge of the rice.
Using the sushi mat, roll the nori tightly around the fillings. Moisten the border with water to seal. Cut the roll into bite-sized pieces using a sharp, wet knife. Serve with soy sauce and wasabi.

recipes.name: Beef Bourguignon
instructions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef chuck pieces and diced bacon in batches until well-browned. Remove and set aside.
In the same pot, sauté sliced carrots, onions, and mushrooms until softened.
Pour red wine into the pot, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom. Bring to a simmer.
Return the beef and bacon to the pot. Add beef broth, minced garlic, thyme, and a bay leaf. Cover and simmer on low heat for several hours until the beef is tender and the flavors are well-developed.

recipes.name: Tacos al Pastor
instructions: Blend achiote paste, soaked guajillo chilies, garlic, onion, lime juice, and spices into a smooth marinade. Coat pork shoulder with the marinade and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Cook the marinated pork on a vertical rotisserie (or grill) until fully cooked and slightly charred.
Thinly slice the cooked pork. Serve on warm corn tortillas with grilled pineapple, chopped onions, and cilantro. Squeeze fresh lime juice over the top before serving.

recipes.name: Lasagna
instructions: Boil lasagna noodles according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef. Add tomato sauce and season with salt, pepper, and Italian herbs. Simmer until thickened.
In a baking dish, layer cooked lasagna noodles, meat sauce, dollops of ricotta cheese, shredded mozzarella, and grated Parmesan. Repeat layers until the dish is filled.
Cover with foil and bake in a preheated oven until the lasagna is bubbly and heated through. Remove foil and bake until the top is golden brown. Let cool slightly before serving.

recipes.name: Chicken Pot Pie
instructions: In a large pot, cook diced chicken breast until no longer pink. Add diced potatoes, carrots, peas, onions, and celery, and cook until vegetables are tender.
In a separate pot, melt butter and whisk in flour to make a roux. Gradually add chicken broth and milk, whisking constantly until thickened.
Stir the chicken and vegetables into the sauce, mixing well.
Pour the mixture into a pie dish. Roll out puff pastry to cover the top, sealing the edges. Cut slits for steam to escape. Bake until the pastry is golden brown and the filling is bubbly.

recipes.name: Mac and Cheese
instructions: Boil macaroni pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.
In a large pot, melt butter and whisk in flour to make a roux. Gradually add milk, whisking constantly until thickened. Stir in shredded cheddar cheese until melted and smooth.
Add the cooked macaroni to the cheese sauce, stirring to coat evenly. Serve immediately, optionally topped with breadcrumbs and baked for a crispy top.

recipes.name: Beef Stew
instructions: In a large pot, brown beef chuck pieces on all sides. Remove and set aside. In the same pot, sauté chopped onions and minced garlic until softened.

Return the beef to the pot. Add chopped carrots, potatoes, beef broth, red wine, bay leaf, thyme, and rosemary. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until the beef and vegetables are tender and the stew has thickened.

recipes.name: Pancakes
instructions: In a bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and sugar. In a separate bowl, whisk together milk, eggs, and melted butter. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.
Heat a griddle or non-stick pan over medium

recipes.name: French Toast
ingredients: 8 slices of bread (preferably slightly stale , like brioche or challah)
maple syrup,powdered sugar , or fresh fruit (for serving )
instructions: Prepare the Batter:in a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk , sugar, vanilla extract, and cinnamon until well combined.
Prepare the Pan :Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. Add a bit of butter and let it melt, coating the pan evenly.
Dip the Bread:Dip each slice of bread into the egg mixture, making sure to coat both sides well but not soak it too long to prevent sogginess.
Cook The Bread:Place the dipped bread slices onto the skillet or griddle. Cook for about 2-3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and crispy.
Serve:Transfer the cooked French toast to a plate and keep warm. Repeat with remaining slices, adding more butter to the pan as needed.
Top and Enjoy:Serve your French toast warm with maple syrup, powdered sugar, fresh fruit, or any toppings you like.
